-- Rose Becomes Chairman of Blue Inc., Sunday Times Reports
-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 2012-06-17T08:21:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-17/rose-becomes-chairman-of-blue-inc-sunday-times-reports.html
Stuart Rose, former chief executive
officer of  Marks & Spencer Group Plc (MKS) , was appointed chairman of
clothing retailer Blue Inc., the  Sunday Times  reported, citing
Rose.  The business has about 200 stores and 2,000 employees,
according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nidaa Bakhsh in London at 
 nbakhsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  